IMPORTANT DIRS AND FILES:
Ubuntu-
/etc/apache2
  Files:
  /etc/apache2/apache2.conf
  
/etc/nginx

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

CHECKING WEB SERVICE
systemctl status apache2   ----- check for apache
systemctl status httpd   ----- check for web server on centOS machine
systemctl status nginx   ----- check for nginx

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

STARTING/STOPPING/RESTARTING SERVICE
sudo systemctl start <apache2 or nginx>
sudo systemctl stop <apache2 or nginx>
sudo systemctl restart <apache2 or nginx>

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

APACHE:

/etc/apache2/apache2.conf
-main config file 

/etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf
-shows where the site will listen ----- ex: <VirtualHost *:80>
-document root = where the website exists ----- ex: /var/www/html

/etc/apache2/sites-available/default-ssl.conf 
-where ssl will be configured


/var/www/html/index.html   or .php
-html for the root of the website (default page)
-for comp it will be the "This file is owned by team #"

